1.write a Python programme to find out biggest value among 2 numbers
# code
a=int(input("Enter First number:"))
b=int(input("Enter Second number:"))
if a>b:
    print(a,"is bigger number")
else:
    print(b,"is bigger number")

#output
Enter First number:4
Enter Second number:9
9 is bigger number


2.Write aPython programme to find out the given number is eveyn or odd number
#code
a=int(input("Enter a number:"))
if a%2==0:
    print(a,"is an even number")
else:
    print(a,"is an odd number")

#output
 Enter a number:8
 8 is an even number


3.Write a programme to accept student number,name and marks in 3 subjects.Calculate the average .Print the students result based on below conditions.
if avg>=75 result is Distinction.
if avg>=60 result is First Class.
if avg>=50 result is Second Class.
if avg>=35 result is Third Class.
otherwise result is Fail.

#code
Studentnumber=int(input("Student Number:"))
name=str(input("Name:"))
m1=int(input("Marks in subject1:"))
m2=int(input("Marks in subject2:"))
m3=int(input("Marks in subject3:"))
total=m1+m2+m3
print("total:",total)
avg=total/3
print("avg:",avg)
if avg>=75:
     print("Distinction")
elif avg>=60:
      print("First Class")
elif avg>=55:
      print("Second Class")
elif avg>=35:
      print("Third Class")
else:
    print("Fail")

#output
Student Number:1
Name:Kavya
Marks in subject1:78
Marks in subject2:80
Marks in subject3:76
total:234
avg:78.0
Distinction
